<div id="review_3094101114" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3094101114" />
    <a title="Rebecca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70058633-rebecca"><img alt="Rebecca" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3094101114?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rebecca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rebecca" href="/user/show/70058633-rebecca">Rebecca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/21086998-a-midnight-clear">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70058633-rebecca?shelf=belgium">belgium</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70058633-rebecca?shelf=christmas">christmas</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/70058633-rebecca?shelf=us">us</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3094101114" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16198731784839969000">I’m surprised that I had never heard of this until a few weeks ago, especially as there is a film starring Ethan Hawke. This is the story of six (mainly young) American men, part of a reconnaissance group stationed in a chateau in the Ardennes forest at the time of the Battle of the Bulge. Personally I preferred the first half of the book, before we really know what is happening, when there is a series of eerie nocturnal events that suggest there is a similar group of German soldiers also statio</span>
  <span id="freeText16198731784839969000" style="display:none">I’m surprised that I had never heard of this until a few weeks ago, especially as there is a film starring Ethan Hawke. This is the story of six (mainly young) American men, part of a reconnaissance group stationed in a chateau in the Ardennes forest at the time of the Battle of the Bulge. Personally I preferred the first half of the book, before we really know what is happening, when there is a series of eerie nocturnal events that suggest there is a similar group of German soldiers also stationed nearby. The tense atmosphere created, as well as the confusion and overall weirdness of the situation was brilliantly done. <br /><br />I liked it less as things became more ‘real’, but that shouldn’t really detract from the actual book (I think I had just written a different book in my own head ahead of time!). Although there are elements that feel very much like a fairytale - the forest setting, the snowy weather, the isolation, the magical Christmas elements - ultimately this becomes a story about the futility of war and the youth, inexperience, fear and confusion of most of its combatants. It can also on occasion be dull, as the group sit around finding things to do and talk about and with the relentless cycle of guard duties, but, as the author writes, this is what much of wartime really is.<br /><br />I don’t read much war literature so this gave me some very different perspectives - the boredom, the confusion, the dirtiness. Overall incredibly moving and sad. Definitely a different and poignant festive read that will stay with me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16198731784839969000" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


