<div id="review_4504149565" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4504149565" />
    <a title="Neon_90s" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/142094003-neon-90s"><img alt="Neon_90s" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1635182038p2/142094003.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4504149565?book_show_action=true">Jan 25, 2022</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Neon_90s" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Neon_90s" href="/user/show/142094003-neon-90s">Neon_90s</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4504149565" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8152827831386066336"> I loved the book. However, and I think it is meant to be that way, at times the progress might feel either too slow or completely rushed. Now, the reason I think is that the book is sort of trying to be a diary type novel, which will without a doubt lead to such disproportionalities as the solider scribbling it down doesn&apos;t have complete control over himself and his current situation. This is my first review so far, and I&apos;m not good at writing overall, but I will try my best to get better as I </span>
  <span id="freeText8152827831386066336" style="display:none"> I loved the book. However, and I think it is meant to be that way, at times the progress might feel either too slow or completely rushed. Now, the reason I think is that the book is sort of trying to be a diary type novel, which will without a doubt lead to such disproportionalities as the solider scribbling it down doesn't have complete control over himself and his current situation. This is my first review so far, and I'm not good at writing overall, but I will try my best to get better as I read and write more :).</span>
  <a data-text-id="8152827831386066336" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

