        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2930381152" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11359395221305649274">A clever reworking of a popular World War I legend that may or may not be true with some definitely not American Heroes channel version of World War II. Definitely some alternative war writing. The ending was expected but as with most endings I always feel as if I have slammed on the brakes as it comes. Maybe it&apos;s supposed to be that way. This may be more true than we let on. </span>
  <span id="freeText11359395221305649274" style="display:none">A clever reworking of a popular World War I legend that may or may not be true with some definitely not American Heroes channel version of World War II. Definitely some alternative war writing. The ending was expected but as with most endings I always feel as if I have slammed on the brakes as it comes. Maybe it's supposed to be that way. This may be more true than we let on. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11359395221305649274" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

